import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['u'], data['v'])
    plt.title('What is the correlation between u and v?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot([data['u'], data['v']])
    ax.set_xticklabels(['u', 'v'])
    plt.title('What is the range of values for u and v?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(['u_mean', 'u_std', 'v_mean', 'v_std'], [data['u'].mean(), data['u'].std(), data['v'].mean(), data['v'].std()])
    ax.set_title('What is the mean and standard deviation of u and v?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(data['u'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.axvline(data['u'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['u'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['u'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['u'].median():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of u?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['v'], bins=20, color='green', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['v'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['v'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['v'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['v'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of v?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
